    "title": "Immediate Requirement Medical Officer at Divi's Laboratories International Enterprises",
    "description": "Divi's Laboratories International Enterprises has an exciting opening for a Medical Officer at our Thane office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Divi's Laboratories International Enterprises:\nDivi's Laboratories International Enterprises is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• BPharm / MPharm / PharmD\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Thane, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Divi's Laboratories International Enterprises!",
